messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path: /printshops/{id}/pricetable/rings

- Are all HTTP methods acceptable for this endpoint? No. The code maps only PUT for the editRingsItem method on this path. (There is a separate POST mapping for adding a new item on the same path, but it is a different operation.)

HTTP methods and acceptance based on the code (for the editRingsItem endpoint at /printshops/{id}/pricetable/rings):
- HEAD: False
- POST: False
- OPTIONS: False
- TRACE: False
- GET: False
- PUT: True
- DELETE: False
- PATCH: False

Explanation:
- The editRingsItem method is explicitly annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/pricetable/rings", method = RequestMethod.PUT), so only PUT is supported for this specific endpoint.
- Although there is another method (addNewRingsItem) that handles POST on the same path, that corresponds to a different operation (adding a new item) and not to the edit operation.
- There is no explicit mapping for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, DELETE, or PATCH for this endpoint, so those methods are not supported by the code for this specific handler.
- The {id} path parameter is correctly used in the path as required.
